Create a data set from a list of objects.

create_dataset.Rd

Meant to be seamlessly compatible with arrow::read_parquet().

Usage

create_dataset(
  x,
  dataset_name,
  engine = arrow::write_parquet,
  ...,
  .file_suffix = NULL,
  .file_ext = NULL
)

Arguments

x

Named list of objects to create an arrow-compatible dataset from

dataset_name

Character scalar. Name of the database folder that should be created.

engine

function The function that will write out the content of x. (Default: arrow::write_parquet)

...

Additional arguments to function specified with 'engine' argument.

.file_suffix, .file_ext

Character scalar. Specify file suffix and file extension, respectively. (Default: NULL)
